<TITLE> Pran Group gets $15 million in IFC loan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 15 (bdnews24.com)  International Finance Corporation has given agro-processing conglomerate Pran Group $15 million, nearly Tk 102 crore, in loan. A World Bank member, IFC gave the seven-year term loan to Pran at a lower rate of interest than that of local banks, the group's executive director Ilyas Mridha said Sunday. He said they had already received half the amount and would spend it on boosting processing capacity, Mridha reporters at a media conference in the city. Pran exports seven products including fruit juice, soft drinks, confectionery, cooking staff and dairy products to more than 70 countries, the official added. The Group employs 15,000 staff and is considering expansion to northeast India, the Middle East and Africa, he said. (US $ 1 = Tk 69) b
